{
  "texts": [
    "The proposed methodology exhibits a heightened capacity for expedited disease detection and precision compared to previous research.",
    "The proposed methodology incorporates a total of five machine learning models, namely Random Forest (RF), K-Nearest Neighbour (KNN), Decision Tree (DT), Extreme Gradient Boosting (XGB), Multilayer Perceptron (MLP), and two deep learning models, Deep Neural Network (DNN), and 1D-Convolutional Neural Network (CNN1D).",
    "The evaluation of the model involved the consideration of various metrics, including accuracy, precision, recall, and the F1-score.",
    "Additionally, a confusion matrix was generated to comprehensively analyze the model's performance concerning established benchmarks within the industry.",
    "The design project selected for this endeavor is the Classifying Heart Sounds Pascal Challenge (CHSPC)."
  ]
}